issues|\n{{context|date=January 2017}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}\n}}\n{{Expand Korean|MBC \ubc29\uc1a1\uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1|date=December 2014}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name           = MBC Entertainment Awards \n| current_awards = 2019 MBC Entertainment Awards\n| description    = Excellence in [[variety show|variety entertainment]]\n| presenter      = [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation]]\n| country        = {{KOR}}\n| location       = [[Seoul]]\n| year           = 1990\n| runtime        = approximately 140 minutes\n}}\n\nThe '''MBC Entertainment Awards''' ({{ko-hhrm|MBC \ubc29\uc1a1\uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1|-\u653e\u9001\u6f14\u85dd\u5927\u8cde}}) is a Korean awards ceremony held annually and sponsored by [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]. The awards ceremony lasts approximately 140 minutes and is shown in two parts on MBC. The ceremony is held at the end of each year.\n\n==Hosts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Year !! Hosts !! Ref.\n|-\n|2001\n|[[Kim Yong-man (comedian)|Kim Yong-man]], {{illm|Lee Kyeong-shil|ko|\uc774\uacbd\uc2e4}}, [[Kim Gook-jin]]\n|\n|-\n|2002\n|[[Lee Kyung-kyu]], [[Park Kyung-lim]]\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|[[Park Soo-hong]], [[Kim Jung-hwa]]\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|[[Park Soo-hong]], [[Kim Won-hee]]\n|\n|-\n|2005\n|{{illm|Jeong Ji-yeong|ko|\uc815\uc9c0\uc601 (\ubc29\uc1a1\uc778)}}, [[Hyun Young]], [[Kim Je-dong]]\n|\n|-\n|2006\n|[[Lee Kyung-kyu]], [[Hyun Young]]\n|\n|-\n|2007\n|[[Lee Hyuk-jae]]\n|\n|-\n|2008\n|[[Lee Hyuk-jae]]\n|\n|-\n|2009\n|[[Lee Hyuk-jae]]\n|\n|-\n|2010\n|[[Park Mi-sun]], {{illm|Lee Kyeong-shil|ko|\uc774\uacbd\uc2e4}}\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|[[Yoon Jong-shin]], [[Park Ha-sun]]\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|[[Kang Ho-dong]], [[Hwang Kwanghee|Kwanghee]], [[Kang So-ra]]\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|[[Gim Gu-ra]], [[Kim Su-ro]], [[So Yi-hyun]]\n|\n|-\n|2014\n|[[Gim Seong-ju (presenter)|Gim Seong-ju]], [[Park Hyung-sik]], [[Kim Sung-ryung]]\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|[[Gim Seong-ju (presenter)|Gim Seong-ju]], [[Gim Gu-ra]], [[Han Chae-ah]]\n|