{"title_page": "McCauley Mountain (New York)", "text_new": "{{distinguish|McCauley Mountain (Ohio, New York)}}\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name = McCauley Mountain\n| photo = MCCAULEY MOUNTAIN, NEW YORK, CHAIR LIFT GIVES TOURISTS A PANORAMIC VIEW IN THE ADIRONDACK FOREST PRESERVE - NARA - 554490.jpg\n| photo_caption = McCauley Mountain chair lift, 1973.  Photo by [[Anne LaBastille]].\n| elevation = {{convert|2280|ft}}\n| prominence = \n| elevation_ref = \n| listing =\n| location = SE of [[Old Forge, New York|Old Forge]], [[New York (state)|New York]], USA\n| range =\n| coordinates = {{coord|43.6925676|-74.9612837|type:mountain_region:US-NY_scale:100000_source:GNIS|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| range_coordinates = \n| coordinates_ref = <ref name=\"gnis\">{{cite gnis\n  | id = 956735\n  | name = McCauley Mountain\n  | accessdate = 2017-12-10 }}</ref>\n| topo = [[United States Geological Survey|USGS]] ''Old Forge''\n| map = New York Adirondack Park#USA\n| map_caption = Location of McCauley Mountain within New York\n| type = \n| age = \n| first_ascent = \n| easiest_route = \n}}\n\n'''McCauley Mountain''' is a [[summit]] and ski resort in the Town of [[Webb, New York|Webb]], [[Herkimer County, New York]]. It is located just outside the hamlet of [[Old Forge, New York|Old Forge]], in the central [[Adirondack Mountains]].\n\nOpened in 1958, it was the hometown hill of Olympic skier [[Hank Kashiwa]].<ref>{{cite book\n | last = Johnson\n | first = Phil\n | authorlink =\n | coauthors =\n | title = The Kingdom of Ahs\n | work =\n | publisher = Skiing\n | date = Feb 1994\n | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=qgD3EKoAXcIC&lpg=PA105-IA1&dq=McCauley%20Mountain%20Old%20Forge&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=false\n | format =\n | doi =\n | accessdate = }}\n</ref>\n\nThe summit of McCauley Mountain is at an altitude of {{convert|2280|ft|m}}. The hill features a {{convert|633|ft|m|adj=on|0}} vertical drop, 21 ski trails of between three and {{convert|5000|ft|m}}, two T-bar tows, two rope tows, and one double chairlift.\n\n==References==\n<references />\n* http://www.mccauleyny.com/mountain.html\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.mccauleyny.com/mountain.html McCauley Mountain Ski Area]\n\n{{Mountains of New York}}\n\n[[Category:Mountains of Herkimer County, New York]]\n[[Category:Mountains of New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Ski areas and resorts in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Herkimer County, New York]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|McCauley Mountain (Ohio, New York)}}\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name = McCauley Mountain\n| photo = MCCAULEY MOUNTAIN, NEW YORK, CHAIR LIFT GIVES TOURISTS A PANORAMIC VIEW IN THE ADIRONDACK FOREST PRESERVE - NARA - 554490.jpg\n| photo_caption = McCauley Mountain chair lift, 1973.  Photo by [[Anne LaBastille]].\n| elevation = {{convert|2280|ft}}\n| prominence = \n| elevation_ref = \n| listing =\n| location = SE of [[Old Forge, New York|Old Forge]], [[New York (state)|New York]], USA\n| range =\n| coordinates = {{coord|43.6925676|-74.9612837|type:mountain_region:US-NY_scale:100000_source:GNIS|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| range_coordinates = \n| coordinates_ref = <ref name=\"gnis\">{{cite gnis\n  | id = 956735\n  | name = McCauley Mountain\n  | accessdate = 2017-12-10 }}</ref>\n| topo = [[United States Geological Survey|USGS]] ''Old Forge''\n| map = New York#USA Adirondack Park#USA\n| map_caption = Location of McCauley Mountain within New York\n| type = \n| age = \n| first_ascent = \n| easiest_route = \n}}\n\n'''McCauley Mountain''' is a [[summit]] and ski resort in the Town of [[Webb, New York|Webb]], [[Herkimer County, New York]]. It is located just outside the hamlet of [[Old Forge, New York|Old Forge]], in the central [[Adirondack Mountains]].\n\nOpened in 1958, it was the hometown hill of Olympic skier [[Hank Kashiwa]].<ref>{{cite book\n | last = Johnson\n | first = Phil\n | authorlink =\n | coauthors =\n | title = The Kingdom of Ahs\n | work =\n | publisher = Skiing\n | date = Feb 1994\n | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=qgD3EKoAXcIC&lpg=PA105-IA1&dq=McCauley%20Mountain%20Old%20Forge&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=false\n | format =\n | doi =\n | accessdate = }}\n</ref>\n\nThe summit of McCauley Mountain is at an altitude of {{convert|2280|ft|m}}. The hill features a {{convert|633|ft|m|adj=on|0}} vertical drop, 21 ski trails of between three and {{convert|5000|ft|m}}, two T-bar tows, two rope tows, and one double chairlift.\n\n==References==\n<references />\n* http://www.mccauleyny.com/mountain.html\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.mccauleyny.com/mountain.html McCauley Mountain Ski Area]\n\n{{Mountains of New York}}\n\n[[Category:Mountains of Herkimer County, New York]]\n[[Category:Mountains of New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Ski areas and resorts in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Herkimer County, New York]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:fix map error", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McCauley_Mountain_(New_York)"}
